Firſt 'Tis certain Money may be ſav'd, which Offices and Officers will ſwallow. The Freeholder deſires to ſee who ſpends the Money he compaſſes by turning the Plow at the Lands-end.
'Tis fine following the Plow in a Sun-ſhine Day, ſucking in, and ſnuffing up the Freſhneſs of the Farth, but Wet and Dry to follow and turn the Plow;
Hic Labor, hoc Opus eſt! And after all your Nine Months Labour carking and caring, you muſt Thraſh out your Compenſation. Will not this naturally make a Man enquire who eats and drinks his 4s. in the Pound out of the Quick Stock?
